    stable 1.3 1.2 1.1 2.0.1
  optional xinetd '' '' for running server

  category network
 attribute server
    source linux-identd-$VERSION.tar.gz
       url http://www.fukt.bth.se/~per/identd/
  homepage http://www.fukt.bth.se/~per/identd/
      desc 'linux-identd is a very small user identification daemon.
linux-identd is a user identification daemon for Linux, 
which implements the Identification Protocol (RFC1413).
This protocol is used to identify active TCP connections.
The daemon listens to TCP port 113 (auth), 
and can be run either as a stand-alone daemon, 
or through inetd.'

build(){
export CEXTRAS="$CFLAGS" &&
make &&
prepare_install
make    install
}

